<body>
	
<header>
	
		
		Determine which conditionals: 'if', 'provided' or 'unless' to use in each questions.
		
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/WB_AW_002.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <p align="left"><b>1	</b><select id="q1"><option>Unless</option><option>If</option><option>Provided</option></select> publishers think that they can sell enough copies, they will not publish a book.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>2	</b><select id="q2"><option>Provided</option><option>Unless</option><option>If</option></select> reviewers like the manuscript, they will pass it on to the commissioning editor.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>3</b>	The book can go for printing <select id="q3"><option>if</option><option>provided</option><option>unless</option></select> it has been thoroughly checked for errors.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>4</b>	Publishers will commission an author <select id="q4"><option>unless</option><option>provided</option><option>if</option></select> they have already been sent a good manuscript.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>5</b>	Blanks have value as coins <select id="q5"><option>if</option><option>provided</option><option>unless</option></select> they have their designs stamped on them.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>6	</b><select id="q6"><option>Unless</option><option>If</option><option>Provided</option></select> blanks have been softened and cleaned, they cannot go to the coining press.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>7</b>	Coins can go into circulation <select id="q7"><option>if</option><option>provided</option><option>unless</option></select> they pass the Trial of the Pyx quality inspection.</p>
  <p align="left"><b>8	</b><select id="q8"><option>If</option><option>Provided</option><option>Unless</option></select> they have defects, coins are sent back to the foundry.</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font size="2"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="rt2001">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">Alternative stages in a process only take place in certain circumstances or depend on the outcome of other stages. The first conditional, with the words, 'if', 'provided' or 'unless', is useful for expressing this kind of relationship between stages.</font>
  </p>
